ne3  ^'A single sphere with texture is shown in ambient green light. The green texture is used to color the surface with a chess board pattern.To see the texture, the material of the surface must have an ambient part that contains green. (Suitable colors are white, gray, yellow, but not red or blue.)For a better understanding of how light color and material properties work together, you should change the color of the ambient light and the ambient part of the surface material. You will find that the surface is rendered in the common color of the ambient light and the ambient part of the material. A black surface means that there is no common color.'! !!B3DDemoSpheres methodsFor: 'demo3' stamp: 'BG 9/2/2002 11:54'!show3    " B3DDemoSpheres new show3"     | view |  self createScene3.  (view := B3DTutorialScenePresenterMorph new)     source: self description: #descriptionScene3;     scene: scene.  view rotateX: 25.4.  view openInSystemWindow.! !!B3DDemoSpheres methodsFor: 'demo4' stamp: 'BG 8/25/2002 13:42'!createLightsForScene4: aScene	| light1 light2 light3 |	light1 := B3DDirectionalLight new.	light1 direction: 100 @ 0 @ 0.     light1 lightColor: (B3DMaterialColor color: (Color r: 0.8 g: 0.15 b: 0.15)).	scene lights add: light1.	light2 := B3DDirectionalLight new.	light2 direction: (120 degreesToRadians cos) * 100  @ (120 degreesToRadians sin * 100) @ 0.     light2 lightColor: (B3DMaterialColor color: (Color r: 0.15 g: 0.8 b: 0.15)).	scene lights add: light2.	light3 := B3DDirectionalLight new.	light3 direction: (240 degreesToRadians cos) * 100  @ (240 degreesToRadians sin * 100) @ 0.     light3 lightColor: (B3DMaterialColor color: (Color r: 0.15 g: 0.15 b: 0.8)).	scene lights add: light3.! !!B3DDemoSpheres methodsFor: 'demo4' stamp: 'BG 8/25/2002 13:18'!createScene4	| camera |	camera _ B3DCamera new.	camera position: 0@0@-6.	camera target: 0@0@0.	camera fov: 15.0.	scene _ B3DScene new.	scene defaultCamera: camera.  